From: Kuniyuki Iwashima <kuniyu@amazon.com>
Date: Wed, 19 Oct 2022 15:35:59 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] inet6: Remove inet6_destroy_sock() in sk->sk_prot->destroy().
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.1.26
Git-commit: b5fc29233d28be7a3322848ebe73ac327559cdb9

commit b5fc29233d28be7a3322848ebe73ac327559cdb9 upstream.

After commit d38afeec26ed ("tcp/udp: Call inet6_destroy_sock()
in IPv6 sk->sk_destruct()."), we call inet6_destroy_sock() in
sk->sk_destruct() by setting inet6_sock_destruct() to it to make
sure we do not leak inet6-specific resources.

Now we can remove unnecessary inet6_destroy_sock() calls in
sk->sk_prot->destroy().

DCCP and SCTP have their own sk->sk_destruct() function, so we
change them separately in the following patches.

